HEADWORD: Childermas day
<hw>Chil"dermas day`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[AS.
<ets>cildam⟦ae⟧sse-d⟦ae⟧g</ets>; <ets>cild</ets> child
+<ets>d⟦ae⟧g</ets> day.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A day (December
28) observed by mass or festival in commemoration of the children slain
by Herod at Bethlehem; -- called also <altname>Holy Innocent's
Day</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

